#bitcoin as the universal answer to all issues usually comes from economic and geographic privilege. Travelling helped me understand this.

You can raise a country with #bitcoin and enable the individual with dollars and/or #bitcoin.

Whenever I have travelled, the poorest people have a universal desire for dollars, even if they know and understand #bitcoin. The same people trying to avoid inflation have the same inherent risk for survival with #bitcoin > rapid devaluation. 

This should not be controversial.

In Venezuela, I saw how the middle-class can Hodl #bitcoin and trade to bolivars to avoid inflation. These were people with "relative" good jobs and better access to technology and education.

I also saw the opposite, people who rely on handouts and hustle to feed their families.

One of the best ways to understand #bitcoin is to travel to as many countries as possible.

You can see how #bitcoin can benefit a country on a macro-scale while at the same time introducing risk on the short-term micro-scale.
